      • getHeader

        public java.util.List<java.lang.String> getHeader()
        Returns the header fields - null if no header exists. The returned list is unmodifiable. Use CsvReader.setContainsHeader(boolean) to enable header parsing. Also note, that the header is only available after first invocation of nextRow().
        Returns:
        the header fields
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - if header parsing is not enabled or nextRow() wasn't called before.

        Returns:
        a CsvRow or null if end of file reached
